# Code Generation

- Generate only the requested scope.
- Do not create unrelated files.
- Do not rewrite complete files for small changes.
- Do not add speculative features.
- Do not add mock data unless requested.
- Do not add excessive comments.
- Do not add generic AI-style abstractions.
- Do not create giant components.
- Do not silently change architecture.
- Search for existing components and utilities before creating new ones.
- Prefer clear project-specific names.
- Keep generated code reviewable and human-sized.
